Design Rules  ("<rulesets/design.xml>")
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

* NestedBlockDepth Rule
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

  Checks for blocks or closures nested more than the limit specified by the <<maxNestedBlockDepth>>
  property. Blocks include <<<if>>>, <<<for>>>, <<<while>>>, <<<switch>>>, <<<try>>>, <<<catch>>>,
  <<<finally>>> and <<<synchronized>>> blocks/statements, as well as closures.

*---------------------+----------------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------+
| <<Property>>        | <<Description>>                                                      | <<Default Value>>      |
*---------------------+----------------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------+
| maxNestedBlockDepth | The maximum number of nesting levels allowed for blocks or closures. | 3                      |
*---------------------+----------------------------------------------------------------------+------------------------+


